KANT BEAT THE ROCK stalked between foes then outside a rival, dropped back two wide then along the rail on the turn and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: IT'S MY HOUSE dueled for the lead from outside, inched ahead in the middle stages, maintained a short lead over ARHAM on the far turn, cleared entering the stretch and held well under urging. AMERICAN ADMIRAL stalked three wide around the first turn, took aim two then three wide on the last turn, chased behind and to the outside of the leader into the final furlong and could not summon the needed late kick in deep stretch. PIROLI stalked the pace on the inside, tipped out at the quarter pole, entered the stretch two to three wide then moved out further and finished willingly for the show honors. ARHAM dueled for the lead from inside, pressed the leader up the backstretch, fought through the far turn before losing touch into the stretch and flattened in the furlong grounds. BRAZENLY settled on the inside then moved to the two path on the clubhouse turn, steered out further on the far turn and came four wide into the drive and lacked a rally.
